FBIS3-50691 "drlat004_r_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 Peru Government Extends State of Emergency in Apurimac Provinces PA0501161894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1456 GMT 5 Jan 94 PA0501161894 Madrid EFE Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Lima, 5 Jan (EFE) -- On 5 January the government extended for 60 days the state of emergency in four provinces of Apurimac Department, in the southern Andean region, to expedite antiterrorist activities. For that reason, civil liberties remain suspended in the Provinces of Chincheros, Andahuaylas, Abancay, and Aymaraes, and the Armed Forces are in charge of internal order. The official newspaper EL PERUANO carried the corresponding decree today. [passage omitted]
